episodes.title: Clown in the Dumps
episodes.plot: Krusty has a crisis of conscience and retires from show business after his father dies before ever approving of his career. Meanwhile, Lisa becomes worried about Homer's health and life expectancy.

episodes.title: The Wreck of the Relationship
episodes.plot: Homer and Bart turn to the open seas to improve their relationship, and Marge becomes a trash talking victim after she drafts Homer's fantasy football team.

episodes.title: Super Franchise Me
episodes.plot: Marge opens a sandwich franchise store after her sandwiches become a huge hit at Springfield Elementary. But running day-to-day at the store proves challenging, especially when the same franchise opens another location across the street.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XXV
episodes.plot: The 25th annual 'Simpsons' Halloween special includes an alternate dimension, a "Clockwork Orange"-style gang led by Moe and a visit from the Tracey Ullman-era Simpsons.

episodes.title: Opposites A-Frack
episodes.plot: An Assemblywoman brought in by Lisa to stop Mr. Burns' fracking operation ends up falling for him as much as he does for her.

episodes.title: Simpsorama
episodes.plot: The Simpsons meet the Planet Express crew, who have come to Springfield in the present to stop them from destroying the future.

episodes.title: Blazed and Confused
episodes.plot: Bart tricks his family into a camping trip at a strange event known as "Blazing Guy" so that he can get revenge on his sadistic new fourth grade teacher.

episodes.title: Covercraft
episodes.plot: Homer forms a cover band with other dads in town when he takes up bass guitar to deal with a mid-life crisis, but the band's modest success is soon overwhelmed by Apu's breakout potential.

episodes.title: I Won't Be Home for Christmas
episodes.plot: Marge kicks Homer out of the house for Christmas after he consoles Moe on Christmas Eve instead of going home.

episodes.title: The Man Who Came to Be Dinner
episodes.plot: An amusement park ride takes the Simpsons to the home planet of Kang and Kodos.

episodes.title: Bart's New Friend
episodes.plot: Homer is hypnotized into believing he's ten years old and ends up stuck in his new age when the hypnotist dies, so he bonds with Bart and refuses to take back the responsibilities of adulthood.

episodes.title: The Musk Who Fell to Earth
episodes.plot: Inventor Elon Musk comes to Springfield, and Homer inspires him with a new idea that could revolutionize Springfield, but winds up costing Mr. Burns a ton of money.

episodes.title: Walking Big & Tall
episodes.plot: Marge tries to get Homer to lose weight. But instead, he finds a support group that encourages him to embrace his largeness.

episodes.title: My Fare Lady
episodes.plot: Marge gets a job as a driver for a transportation app service, while Moe is forced to work as a janitor at the nuclear plant after Homer causes the bar to go bankrupt.

episodes.title: The Princess Guide
episodes.plot: Moe falls in love with a Nigerian princess whose father is working out a uranium deal with Mr. Burns.

episodes.title: Sky Police
episodes.plot: The congregation, led by Marge, is forced to resort to gambling in order to collect money to fix the church, which Chief Wiggum destroyed with a jet pack he received by mistake.

episodes.title: Waiting for Duffman
episodes.plot: After "Duffman" retires, Homer wins a reality competition to become his replacement. But his contract states that he cannot drink beer, which gives him a new perspective on alcohol.

episodes.title: Peeping Mom
episodes.plot: Marge decides to follow Bart everywhere until he confesses to being involved in a bulldozer crash. Meanwhile, Homer ignores Santa's Little Helper when Ned gets a new dog.

episodes.title: The Kids Are All Fight
episodes.plot: The story of Bart and Lisa's rivalry is told when Homer finds an old film strip.

episodes.title: Let's Go Fly a Coot
episodes.plot: Bart takes up smoking e-cigarettes to impress Milhouse's cousin Annika while the rest of the family learns about Grampa's days in the Air Force.

episodes.title: Bull-E
episodes.plot: Bart gets bullied at a school dance, so Marge gets an anti-bullying law passed, which results in Homer being put in therapy for bulling Ned.

episodes.title: Mathlete's Feat
episodes.plot: Groundskeeper Willie becomes the coach of the mathletes, Lisa and other kids from Springfield Elementary compete against Waverly Hills Elementary.
